  "prompt": "How do Michael Jordan grow taller?",
  "response": "Michael Jordan's height, officially listed at 6 feet 6 inches (1.98 meters), is predominantly a result of genetics rather than specific actions he took to grow taller. Height is primarily determined by genetic factors inherited from parents. By the time he was in high school and began his basketball career, he had already reached his adult height.\n\nIt's worth noting that although athletes may engage in strength training and other fitness regimes that can improve their posture and overall physique, these practices do not actually increase height once a person has finished growing. Most individuals stop gaining height in their late teens to early twenties when growth plates close.\n\nJordan's height was an asset in basketball, contributing to his exceptional ability on the court, but he did not actively do anything to increase his height during his career or afterward.",
